Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.65,0:26:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is it suddenly stopped? We don't all still think the world is flat, do we? Do we? She thinks the world is flat. She thinks the world is flat, but the rest of us don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.81,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, when it comes to spirituality and religion, most people still think the world is flat. I mean, that's really their level of understanding. It's nowhere, nowhere at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we are going to, in this particular study we're doing now, address the evolution of consciousness throughout all of mankind, mankind's history, and try to track out why and what is holding it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.89,0:27:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, how come it's not up to 300, you know, 400? What's keeping it, why isn't it 500? Why isn't the unconditional love prevailing in our society? Why doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.66,0:27:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the kind of things that we're...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.08,0:27:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.08,0:27:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so I guess we're all reassembled this afternoon so we can resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.20,0:27:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking about the nature of consciousness as the evolution of consciousness is experienced through this particular track of historical memory here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.22,0:27:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And one thing that was peculiar, the other thing that was peculiar about the sudden presence was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.22,0:27:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the feeling of completion, the feeling of not needing anything more.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.60,0:28:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And that prevails to this day. If somebody says, what do you want for Christmas? I have to think, what does want mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.02,0:28:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's really meaningless. There's no wanting anything. There's no lack, there's no need, there's no desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.12,0:28:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,January 10th, 1965, when I really got hit by the presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.12,0:28:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at that moment, in that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.12,0:28:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,all that's considered essentially human disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.47,0:28:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire for fame, fortune, money, power, influence over others,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.66,0:28:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,all these strange melodies that afflict people seemed to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.08,0:28:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They just disappeared. It wasn't through any kind of heroic spiritual effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.08,0:28:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They disappeared of their own nature and have not reappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.56,0:28:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.56,0:28:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then I was left in the world devoid of what drives most people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.56,0:29:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to figure out what to do from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.72,0:29:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do from here? Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.75,0:29:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And people would say, well, you've got to pay attention to reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.75,0:29:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and get back to practice, and make some money, and all this kind of thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.88,0:29:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it didn't make too much sense to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.88,0:29:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood the words, sort of, but it didn't ever have any,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.88,0:29:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't any inner reality for it to hang into, to activate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.00,0:29:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.00,0:29:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be anxious about your own survival to worry about such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.00,0:29:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But, anyway, over some years that I retired from the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.51,0:29:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I did relearn how to relate to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.51,0:29:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and one handy way of doing that was watching television.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.80,0:29:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't own a television set.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.80,0:29:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't read newspapers or magazines or any such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.92,0:29:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just spent all the time meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.92,0:29:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I discovered that if you watch TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.28,0:30:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find out what's been happening in the world the last ten years, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.72,0:30:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember there was Princess something-or-other.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.72,0:30:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very famous on the front page of everything that went in the grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.72,0:30:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There she was in front of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.72,0:30:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know who that she was, or any of those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.82,0:30:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was a relearning of how to be in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.85,0:30:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When those things happen, people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.56,0:30:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,well, what is that like when it happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.56,0:30:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In the high 500s, you go into this incredible being in love with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.56,0:30:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go through the phase of crying at the drop of a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.56,0:30:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at two people looking at each other tenderly,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.91,0:30:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the love just knocks you out, and you start to weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.91,0:30:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you go through a stage of crying and weeping over beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.91,0:30:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you hear a piece of music, and it just lays you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.91,0:30:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We were speaking someplace or other,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.26,0:30:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and she turned on the TV, and this incredible symphony,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.26,0:31:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible music came on, and I just lay on the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.45,0:31:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't get off the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.45,0:31:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty was so knocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.45,0:31:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It just knocked you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.45,0:31:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.45,0:31:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In the high 500s, the realization of the beauty and the perfection of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.45,0:31:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.45,0:31:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The intrinsic beauty of each thing shines forth in its radiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.45,0:31:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you weep with its beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.66,0:31:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there is that difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.10,0:31:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In monasteries and places like that, it's common.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.10,0:31:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they cry for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.13,0:31:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say anything nice to them or loving or show them a rose or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.13,0:31:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.13,0:31:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't rely on them to get much work done.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.13,0:31:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the high 500s, you see the beauty and the perfection of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.68,0:31:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything knocks you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.00,0:32:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a period of time where everything knocks you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.00,0:32:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're not careful, even that knocks you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.00,0:32:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see a little tree or a weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.03,0:32:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person would say that's just a weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.03,0:32:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you see is the incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.03,0:32:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the weed as a magnificent sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.03,0:32:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see its incredible beauty and perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.03,0:32:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the incredible perfection of the weed standing forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.09,0:32:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the design of each thing shining forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.09,0:32:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intrinsic beauty of creation shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.22,0:32:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the perfection of all things sort of takes hold in the high 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.08,0:32:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at 600, you run into sort of the near death experience kind of experience I had
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.08,0:32:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,where the intensity of the bliss is such you cannot function.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.08,0:32:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot function.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.15,0:32:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need to eat, drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.15,0:32:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The body functions just come to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.44,0:33:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only the radiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.76,0:33:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you're outside of time, there's no way of knowing whether weeks, months,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.92,0:33:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether it's even the same lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.49,0:33:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound crazy, but you don't even know if it's the same lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.49,0:33:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And whether you survive or not really depends on having people around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.52,0:33:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, if it weren't for the presence of a loving, if it wasn't for Susan,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.91,0:33:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably wouldn't even eat for weeks at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.91,0:33:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.91,0:33:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It just never comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.91,0:33:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It just doesn't come to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.91,0:33:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it's good if you do intense spiritual work to be aligned with a spiritual group.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.80,0:33:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Be aligned with a spiritual group.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.80,0:33:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because any spiritual practice you do, you can just suddenly take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.80,0:33:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.80,0:33:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because spiritual evolution is both longitudinal like this, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.80,0:33:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of like, you know, the Dow Jones or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.96,0:33:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As the years go by, you go ups and downs and ups and downs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.96,0:34:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you gradually evolve higher and higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.99,0:34:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's sudden breaks where you suddenly go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.99,0:34:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You can suddenly go vertically just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.99,0:34:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be playing with a mantra that somebody, some great guru whispered in your ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.15,0:34:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get $350, you get $550 or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.24,0:34:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And all your life you're out there waiting in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.24,0:34:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, bam, instantly, you're out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.24,0:34:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're out by yourself and nobody knows what's going on with you, they could think he's going catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.47,0:34:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I went catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.47,0:34:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I went like that in this divine bliss state.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.47,0:34:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw the world would think he's catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.47,0:34:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would take me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.47,0:34:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.47,0:34:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrendered that one to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.47,0:34:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if they think I'm catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.47,0:34:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're going to haul you off to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.47,0:34:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting on a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.47,0:34:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.47,0:34:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in this bliss state.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.04,0:34:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn't get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.04,0:35:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, well, they'll see this person sitting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.04,0:35:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.04,0:35:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.04,0:35:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And the police will take you to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.04,0:35:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.04,0:35:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And the doctor will examine you and say, he's catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.04,0:35:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.04,0:35:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they will put you in a mental hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.04,0:35:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.04,0:35:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll probably shoot you full of Thorazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.04,0:35:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.04,0:35:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which I am is not reachable by Thorazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.04,0:35:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sedate the hell out of the body and the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.04,0:35:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not the body and the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.04,0:35:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't care what you do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.04,0:35:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.04,0:35:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like beyond all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.04,0:35:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you didn't have friends around to see that you ate and got off the rock, you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.04,0:35:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,could still eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.04,0:35:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You could still be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.04,0:35:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'm kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.04,0:35:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, after Ramana Maharshi, Ramana Maharshi was 15 or 16 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.04,0:35:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was just an ordinary religious Hindu fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.04,0:35:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not overly religious or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.04,0:35:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day, he suddenly felt like he was dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.43,0:35:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And he fell down in a weak state.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.43,0:35:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And he realized he had just died.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.43,0:36:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then he went into this state of bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.52,0:36:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this state of bliss, he just sat there, I guess, for some days and weeks and was all
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.55,0:36:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,bitten up by insects and hadn't eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.55,0:36:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was discovered by some people who did have some spiritual erudition and recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.84,0:36:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the state he was in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.84,0:36:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was unable to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.84,0:36:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even talk for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.84,0:36:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It took him two years to relearn how to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.16,0:36:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if he had not been surrounded by a couple of spiritual, spiritually oriented
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.12,0:36:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,people, you know, I guess they could have put him in a mental hospital in India for
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.12,0:36:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced serious catatonia or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.50,0:36:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to have some people who know what you're doing, you know, because it can happen
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.50,0:36:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.50,0:36:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just why?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.50,0:36:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your spiritual orientation is to go in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.50,0:36:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you are what makes the technique work.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.11,0:36:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the mantra that gets you to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.11,0:36:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the spinning the prayer wheel or getting funny haircuts, sitting cross-legged
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.11,0:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and breathing in strange and peculiar ways from one side of the nose to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.11,0:37:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.11,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of who you are and your intention that that should get you to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what gets you to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.71,0:37:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Ramana Maharshi it says, God feels sorry for you after a while and picks you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.71,0:37:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,up and takes you into his arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.71,0:37:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,After all that strange breathing and staring at the sun and starving yourself and ringing
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.71,0:37:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,bells and chanting mantras and all this weird stuff, the strange haircuts, all the bizarre
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.80,0:37:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,things, and the bells and whistles that goes with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.96,0:37:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are not what's divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.96,0:37:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's divine is the entity that is empowering those things to bring them closer to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.02,0:37:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See people going to the holy land.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.02,0:37:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how holy that holy land is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.02,0:38:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,After all the killing, warfare, bloodshed, murder, hatred, loathing, persecution, all
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.02,0:38:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of this holy place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.02,0:38:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I never calculated the energy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.02,0:38:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be afraid to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.02,0:38:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what the energy of the holy place is in this earth or life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.46,0:38:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Like God's interested in real estate, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.46,0:38:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This little strip of this country is holy to God, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.46,0:38:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the things we want to do in the Eye of the Eye is improve God's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.56,0:38:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of my functions here, according to, just to clear up his name on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.77,0:38:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.48,0:38:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because God gets blamed for all the negativity in the world, don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.60,0:38:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of retaliation, the God of fear, the God of jealousy, hatred, and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.60,0:38:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This map of consciousness we have over on one side, the view of God that that particular
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.66,0:38:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness is agreeable with.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.66,0:38:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.66,0:39:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If your level of consciousness is way down at the bottom, then a God who's angry at you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.66,0:39:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and vengeful because he's got low self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.66,0:39:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And gets upset if you worship graven images or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.79,0:39:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And strikes you dead in your whole city.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.79,0:39:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Burns it up and fit of paranoid jealousy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.97,0:39:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You lose control of himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.97,0:39:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroys whole cities and civilizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.97,0:39:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There, take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.97,0:39:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, most of the world believes in God like that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.73,0:39:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I start these lectures, usually, usually I have this map of consciousness and a transparency,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.73,0:39:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which I forgot the date.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.86,0:39:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.86,0:39:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Projected up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.86,0:39:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first thing I bring to people's attention is that God is at the top of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.86,0:39:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.92,0:39:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And people say, oh, that's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.92,0:39:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.92,0:39:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the world believes that God is at the bottom of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.02,0:39:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.02,0:39:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.02,0:39:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.02,0:39:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The God that's paranoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.02,0:40:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That needs, uh, it goes to Thorazine to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.12,0:40:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Worried that his power is being undermined by people with all their strange rituals and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.40,0:40:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.40,0:40:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You eat meat on Friday, I mean, you know, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.49,0:40:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't wear a certain kind of hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.49,0:40:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you do wear a certain kind of hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.68,0:40:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine Jesus getting upset because you wore a hat in church or you didn't wear a hat in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.68,0:40:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,church.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.68,0:40:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was young, all the ladies had to wear a hat in church.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.68,0:40:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because God would be upset if you didn't wear a, if ladies didn't wear a hat in church.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.10,0:40:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was sacrilegious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sacrilegious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.10,0:40:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.36,0:40:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we got all that negativity, you know, incorporated into our culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.36,0:40:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sacrilegious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.36,0:40:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, God's gonna be upset with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.61,0:40:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, God's gonna be upset with you if you wear a hat or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.54,0:40:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't even know if you're wearing a hat, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.70,0:40:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you like to think that God does notice that you're wearing a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.70,0:40:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the hat that you're wearing, so how would he notice it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.70,0:40:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.70,0:41:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is can't notice its own self, isness, because isness is isness, and not that which
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.92,0:41:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,witnesses isness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.92,0:41:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.92,0:41:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Identity knows only its own identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.21,0:41:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore comprehend what God is all about when I say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.63,0:41:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand that identity is its own identity and nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.63,0:41:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing arises as a creation out of its own essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.63,0:41:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is complete and total and perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.45,0:41:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so then that, if that is so, then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.48,0:41:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What goes on with human consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.48,0:41:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it not so for all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.48,0:41:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.48,0:41:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk today a little bit about karma, karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.01,0:41:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing I want to address in the book I'm working on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.01,0:41:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at the spiritual ignorance that goes on,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.01,0:41:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you see ignorance in all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.01,0:41:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said the world is flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.01,0:41:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people still believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.01,0:41:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not too many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.01,0:41:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But in religion and spirituality, a lot of people are really at the level of thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.01,0:41:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.01,0:42:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That there's been no examination, reexamination of things that are passed down generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.01,0:42:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's like it's, you know, passed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.01,0:42:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it's, it's written in rock, you know, written in eternal cement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.81,0:42:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because some prophet said it someplace or other and it was misquoted and now it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.26,0:42:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,prevailed as law.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.26,0:42:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not prevailed as law.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.26,0:42:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So mankind then is held by fallacious laws that he believes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.09,0:42:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Fallacious belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.09,0:42:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When you calibrate the energy fields of what prevails in mankind's spiritual belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.73,0:42:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it will, you'll feel like training.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.73,0:42:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The beliefs in things that are just grossly negative, just grossly make your arm go weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.02,0:42:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.02,0:42:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So fallacy then gains its influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.95,0:42:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,By repetition.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.95,0:42:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.75,0:43:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By not knowing the difference between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.75,0:43:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Not knowing the difference between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.75,0:43:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that's true should certainly stand up to kinesiologic test of truth, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.75,0:43:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing should go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.42,0:43:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We would say at least it's not exactly up to snuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.42,0:43:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of what goes on in the world does not come up to snuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.80,0:43:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does all this perpetuate itself then, generation after generation?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.96,0:43:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have to look at how does consciousness transmit itself from lifetime to lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd have to look at what has historically been called karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.08,0:43:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, karma is one thing and reincarnation is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.81,0:43:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When people get into discussions, they confuse the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.81,0:43:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talk about karma, we're not talking about reincarnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.81,0:43:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a different subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.81,0:43:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To re-embody oneself is...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.81,0:44:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a different subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.97,0:44:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma has to do with consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.26,0:44:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with embodiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.26,0:44:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All the world's religions teach karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.28,0:44:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All the world's religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.28,0:44:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't call it karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.28,0:44:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity, the world, doesn't use the word karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.28,0:44:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus Christ says that you shall reap as you sow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.28,0:44:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He certainly tells you to avoid sin because the consequences are not too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.41,0:44:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And warns us that below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.05,0:44:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,will take you into unfortunate places when you leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.24,0:44:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the world's great spiritual traditions and religions all teach the one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.24,0:44:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That the choices we make, the options we make,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.82,0:44:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,will determine
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.88,0:44:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,future experience of that aspect of the human which survives its physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.88,0:44:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no question that...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.88,0:45:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in traditional Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.33,0:45:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity, there is no mention of other than one...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.33,0:45:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a presumption you only have one body.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.33,0:45:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, after you leave this body,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.43,0:45:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you will go someplace befitting what your choices in this world determine for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.43,0:45:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Heaven, hell, purgatory, or limbo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.43,0:45:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't many other places that cover this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.43,0:45:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There are options when you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.43,0:45:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, herein comes the fear of the Christian then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.71,0:45:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that there will be a great judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.71,0:45:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And this judge may take a very negative view of your behaviors in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.71,0:45:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the consequences will be unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.71,0:45:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have this negative God that we fear will judge us at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.80,0:45:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This God is external to the reality of who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.34,0:45:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to be judged by God,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.69,0:45:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to be this and God would have to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.69,0:46:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that implies a separation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.69,0:46:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There would have to be a separation between the reality of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.69,0:46:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this kind of entity that sits out there and judges you,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.69,0:46:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and then takes action against you via force.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.69,0:46:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because throwing people into hell with a fry is sort of force, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.69,0:46:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Not exactly friendly, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.20,0:46:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there is a presumption and a separation,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.52,0:46:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the projection of man's own negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.52,0:46:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, Sigmund Freud,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.59,0:46:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and Moses and Amathia,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.59,0:46:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud calibrates at 499,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.81,0:46:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,he correctly deduced that the negative images of God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.81,0:46:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,were projections of man's own unconscious guilt and fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.32,0:46:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, because they're just projections from the unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.32,0:46:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they have no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.36,0:46:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And there he was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.36,0:46:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he made the error.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.36,0:46:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, therefore, there is no God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.36,0:46:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was a jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.36,0:47:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What he should have said is,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.36,0:47:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,these projections from man's unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.36,0:47:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,create a false image of God as a very negative being,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.45,0:47:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and that particular being doesn't have reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.45,0:47:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.45,0:47:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why Freud stands at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.45,0:47:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung, who calibrates at 520,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.45,0:47:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,validated the reality of man's spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.45,0:47:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 499 is the great barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.84,0:47:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very unusual and very hard to get over 499,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.03,0:47:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and not many people do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.03,0:47:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the great intellect stopped at 499,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.60,0:47:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's a jump to a different paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.60,0:47:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to jump from the linear to the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.60,0:47:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to see the reality of the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.60,0:47:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Carl Jung, who calibrates at about 520,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.60,0:47:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,validated the spiritual reality of man,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.67,0:47:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore calibrates an entire Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.67,0:47:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the God that Freud threw out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.76,0:47:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was the same one I threw out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.76,0:47:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when I saw the totality of man's suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.76,0:48:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw out any God that could be the cause of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.76,0:48:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the misunderstanding was
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.76,0:48:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was ascribing to God, blaming God
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.76,0:48:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is the creation of the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.76,0:48:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the human ego that creates war and pestilence and suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.76,0:48:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the miseries that we blame on God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.76,0:48:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When you understand the nature of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.56,0:48:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the thought that negativity could be some kind of a weird reality
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.81,0:48:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that emanates from that divinity is absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.81,0:48:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But when people have had no personal experience of the presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.81,0:48:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they are willing to believe almost anything that you tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.81,0:48:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.81,0:48:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What does determine then what happens at death?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.60,0:48:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the spirit all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.60,0:48:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said that everything and anything on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.66,0:48:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,gives forth an energy and a vibration of frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.66,0:48:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We can calibrate that frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.66,0:48:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We can calibrate the frequency and energy of anything and everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.66,0:48:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,every saint that ever lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.66,0:49:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,every sentence pronounced by every guru who ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.33,0:49:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of truth of that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.33,0:49:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.66,0:49:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all of us are carried with us a spiritual body,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.66,0:49:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the frequency of which is actually calibratable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.66,0:49:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And its fate depends then completely on what its calibrated energy level is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.69,0:49:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to give you a different picture of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.98,0:49:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a different picture of how the universe works.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.98,0:49:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing, because it is only what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.27,0:49:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not what it is because of something else,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.27,0:49:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but only because of its own essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.48,0:49:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.48,0:49:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You only...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.48,0:49:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what it is out of its expression of its divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.48,0:49:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing itself as what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.48,0:49:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.88,0:49:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the universe is working is not like linear causality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.88,0:49:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where a billion balls are hitting each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.88,0:50:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it's almost like little tiny magnets
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.43,0:50:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,all circulating around in a great big vast space.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.84,0:50:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the movement and the direction and the influences
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.84,0:50:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are all emanating from the essence of what each thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.84,0:50:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.84,0:50:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.07,0:50:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like its polarity, its power,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.36,0:50:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is interacting with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.36,0:50:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.09,0:50:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Like little iron filings in a giant electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.09,0:50:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Each filing lines itself up depending on its polarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.09,0:50:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,its degree of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.09,0:50:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,how much iron is in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.09,0:50:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.38,0:50:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no arbitrary field knocking this little magnet this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.38,0:50:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad little magnet knocking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.73,0:50:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.73,0:50:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is being where it is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.73,0:50:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because out of the essence of its own divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.73,0:50:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot be otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.73,0:50:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is expressing itself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.89,0:50:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and like a cloud floats through the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.89,0:51:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the geometric pressure and the winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.21,0:51:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is the spirit body
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.21,0:51:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course, at least the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.21,0:51:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody experiences their own physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.21,0:51:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I might as well tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.21,0:51:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody experiences their own physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.11,0:51:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment of death, wham, you're out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.11,0:51:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You witness the body laying there
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.11,0:51:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the car just ran over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.11,0:51:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of interesting, but not too.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.20,0:51:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And anything catastrophic you experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.80,0:51:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.80,0:51:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's horribly painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.15,0:51:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.15,0:51:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's fatal,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.65,0:51:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,yep, you're out in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.65,0:51:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You witness it happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.65,0:51:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what happens to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.65,0:51:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now what happens to you depends on the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.65,0:51:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the frequency and the vibration of where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.65,0:51:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're now a cloud in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.65,0:51:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.68,0:51:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,gravitate to the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.68,0:51:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is your natural space to be in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.68,0:51:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.68,0:51:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if the heavens calibrate just like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.68,0:52:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and they do, the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.68,0:52:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.68,0:52:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you will gravitate to where,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.68,0:52:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,say, everybody is like a cork in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.97,0:52:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.97,0:52:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You rise to the level of your own buoyancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.97,0:52:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no arbitrary god out there
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.36,0:52:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing this cork to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.36,0:52:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each cork, when you think of what would
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.36,0:52:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,divine justice be,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.36,0:52:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,divine justice would have to be absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.36,0:52:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing automatically,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.48,0:52:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its own nature
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.48,0:52:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nature of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.48,0:52:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is exactly where it is due to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.48,0:52:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,its own expression of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.48,0:52:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.48,0:52:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That is absolute,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.74,0:52:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.74,0:52:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the justice of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.05,0:52:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that only that which you have
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.47,0:52:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely deserved of yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.47,0:52:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,can possibly be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.47,0:52:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing arbitrary outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.47,0:52:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,has any influence over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.47,0:53:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, just from the viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.84,0:53:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of the science of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.84,0:53:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.84,0:53:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the negative gods
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.84,0:53:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have no power over you whatsoever,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.84,0:53:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because, first of all, they have no existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.84,0:53:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us determines their own fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.84,0:53:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,their own future.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.84,0:53:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So every choice that we make
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.84,0:53:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from moment to moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.84,0:53:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.84,0:53:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,changes the buoyancy of our cork.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.68,0:53:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if our Holy Spirit is like a
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.68,0:53:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,etheric cork,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.66,0:53:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes where it's going to go in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.66,0:53:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its own buoyancy,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.66,0:53:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,its own power,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.66,0:53:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,its own frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.66,0:53:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, a spirit that radiates at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.82,0:53:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to go to a different place
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.82,0:53:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,than a spirit that radiates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.82,0:53:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,190 is probably going to land in a space
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.04,0:53:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where there's militarism
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.17,0:54:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and war and pridefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.17,0:54:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so each spirit's going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.91,0:54:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where it needs to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.91,0:54:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where it wants to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.91,0:54:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to go where it is decided
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.91,0:54:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by its own actions to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.42,0:54:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If that is so,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.42,0:54:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.42,0:54:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the drama that we see that goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.68,0:54:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the human evolution of society, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.68,0:54:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the outcropping,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.68,0:54:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the acting out of these levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.68,0:54:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To get over 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.73,0:54:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to cross the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.73,0:54:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to cross over the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.73,0:54:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.73,0:54:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.73,0:54:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the population is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.76,0:54:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get above 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.10,0:54:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,200 means out of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.77,0:54:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,out of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.77,0:54:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,out of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.77,0:54:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.00,0:54:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One is even willing to give up their life
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.00,0:54:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for something greater than the personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.00,0:55:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see war is the great opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.00,0:55:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for spirits to come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.06,0:55:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,walk into a rain of bullets,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.48,0:55:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because they believe in the divinity of the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.57,0:55:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the kamikaze pilots all went
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.89,0:55:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to a great place when they left.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.89,0:55:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You willingly give up your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.12,0:55:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or the faith that you believe is God,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.12,0:55:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because they thought the emperor was
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.12,0:55:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the representation of the sun god.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.12,0:55:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.24,0:55:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You cross over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.24,0:55:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You cross over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.24,0:55:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You come out of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.24,0:55:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you cross over 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.24,0:55:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you want integrity for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.24,0:55:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.24,0:55:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.44,0:55:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.72,0:55:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I just knew intuitively, spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.72,0:55:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the kamikaze pilots, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.72,0:55:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see them,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.72,0:55:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.13,0:55:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for the love of themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.13,0:55:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for their love of each other and their country,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.13,0:55:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the love of their emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.13,0:55:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they surrender their actual life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.13,0:55:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which they believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.13,0:55:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's a profound spiritual step.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.13,0:56:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't care what it means politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.96,0:56:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,now we're talking spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.96,0:56:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritually, it's a profound step.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.96,0:56:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see all that goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.09,0:56:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the human endeavor, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.09,0:56:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is really an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.09,0:56:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.09,0:56:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There is some point in the evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.09,0:56:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.09,0:56:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Every man here who can remember past lives
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.86,0:56:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,will remember a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.86,0:56:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you had to stand up,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.86,0:56:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,walk out of the trenches,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.86,0:56:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and face certain death.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.86,0:56:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you had to do it for the emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.86,0:56:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to do it for Nero,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.86,0:56:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to do it for the Roman Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.21,0:56:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to do it for Christ, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.21,0:56:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that moment is a profound moment
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.50,0:56:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because you cross over.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.50,0:56:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.50,0:56:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,when people go over 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.95,0:56:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,they tend to remember past lives, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.95,0:56:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.95,0:56:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, past lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.95,0:56:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it difficult how people can have
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.95,0:56:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a really profound, solid spiritual understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.95,0:56:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,or a belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.95,0:56:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,without comprehending karma
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.95,0:56:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because it would leave you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.95,0:57:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with no understanding at all
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.95,0:57:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of what happens in human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.95,0:57:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a little baby's born,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.95,0:57:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and at two months old,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.95,0:57:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it gets hit in the head by a crock pot
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.30,0:57:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and it also has cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.30,0:57:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It has AIDS when it's born,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.30,0:57:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and it screams and goes into
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.30,0:57:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,an epileptic fit and dies, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.30,0:57:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a child do to deserve that,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.49,0:57:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.75,0:57:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect can't believe in God,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.75,0:57:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,really can't believe in God,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.75,0:57:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,really can't believe in God,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.75,0:57:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no rationality,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.75,0:57:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,no rationality,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.75,0:57:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,no rationality to what you witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.75,0:57:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,no explanation whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.75,0:57:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without understanding karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.00,0:57:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you look without any explanation whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.00,0:57:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody that isn't an atheist isn't too bright
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.68,0:57:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you look at things with the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.02,0:57:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be stupid to think that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.02,0:57:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of God is in charge
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.02,0:57:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the wickedness that prevails
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.02,0:57:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in our human civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.47,0:57:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there would have to be some explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.47,0:57:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because once you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.47,0:57:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how the universe and the mind of God work,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.47,0:57:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,everything works together perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.47,0:57:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolute perfection and cohesion
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.47,0:58:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.47,0:58:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no outness to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.47,0:58:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no little baby accidentally
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.47,0:58:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,gets dropped on its head
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.47,0:58:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and born with AIDS
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.47,0:58:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and dies to sell the salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.95,0:58:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Africa is full of it, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.16,0:58:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,By the millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.52,0:58:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They're born into starvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.52,0:58:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,malnutrition,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.52,0:58:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they have convulsions,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.87,0:58:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they get AIDS and starve to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.87,0:58:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother who's dying of AIDS
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.22,0:58:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,can't even lift their little bodies anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.22,0:58:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She just lays them by the side of the road
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.22,0:58:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and walks off.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.22,0:58:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The flies come.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.22,0:58:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the explanation for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.80,0:58:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.80,0:58:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that accidental?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.80,0:58:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.02,0:58:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing accidental in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.02,0:58:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.02,0:58:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,no accident is possible in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.02,0:58:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.02,0:58:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,where everything interacts
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.02,0:58:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with everything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.02,0:58:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,no accident is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.12,0:58:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,From the viewpoint of Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.08,0:58:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,linear reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.59,0:58:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this thing causes this
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.84,0:59:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.84,0:59:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,From more advanced consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.16,0:59:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.40,0:59:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.40,0:59:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.60,0:59:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.60,0:59:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not because it's caused by this here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.20,0:59:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but unless this was here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.20,0:59:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this couldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.20,0:59:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.20,0:59:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.29,0:59:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this can be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.29,0:59:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is not causing that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.29,0:59:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.29,0:59:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.39,0:59:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not causing it to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.99,0:59:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So if a soul wills itself into hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.99,0:59:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it does so of its own volition,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.99,0:59:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,not because some angry God-like figure
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.99,0:59:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,picked you up and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.21,0:59:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,well, you stole from the supermarket,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.21,0:59:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're going to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.21,0:59:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And throws you a little spirit body
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.21,0:59:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,down there to fry.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.21,0:59:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.21,0:59:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that's really ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.21,0:59:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world lives in fear of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.21,0:59:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and certainly the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.21,0:59:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,addresses that profound ignorance,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.21,0:59:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which prevails
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.21,0:59:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in man's consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.21,0:59:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.21,0:59:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was really the first one
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.21,0:59:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that brought it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.21,1:00:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,really brought it up
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.21,1:00:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to be looked at
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.21,1:00:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and reexamined
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.21,1:00:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as such a negative image of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.37,1:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a possible reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.37,1:00:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Course concludes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.37,1:00:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not even a possible reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.37,1:00:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.37,1:00:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an absurdity,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.37,1:00:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but because it's repeated so often,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.37,1:00:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,generation after generation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.37,1:00:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.85,1:00:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind is very influenced
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.85,1:00:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by the herd.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.85,1:00:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So if everybody in your society
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.85,1:00:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,believes a certain thing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.85,1:00:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is a certain thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.85,1:00:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very hard not to think
