Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.71,1:51:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't happen tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.54,1:51:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't happen next week. It can only happen right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.84,1:51:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the real power that leads to enlightenment, it rises out of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.84,1:51:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:28.45,1:51:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of your love for the leader of North China arises your own salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.51,1:51:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you only discover the power of your love when you express it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.06,1:51:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.06,1:51:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience it and you realize divinity is that which is within you,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.06,1:51:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of which your own existence arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.06,1:51:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So our salvation, as a group here, depends on our saving China.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.98,1:51:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise we don't know the truth of our own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.01,1:51:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's put it to the test.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.01,1:52:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason spirituality has worked for me, and it works incredibly well,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.20,1:52:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is because I always put it to the test.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.58,1:52:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Either it is or it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.58,1:52:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.68,1:52:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear preachers talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.78,1:52:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that they haven't even experienced.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.78,1:52:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What I've done is somebody on the road to someplace in history who cares.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.78,1:52:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what happens to me on the road to going outside here right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.78,1:52:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where reality is.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.93,1:52:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is not somewhere a couple thousand years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.93,1:52:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all popcock.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.98,1:52:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience the reality and the power of our own divinity right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.10,1:52:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a break, and then we'll have questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.10,1:52:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and China's enough to work on everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.29,1:52:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start on Africa next year.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.38,1:53:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to recapitulate creation throughout all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.38,1:53:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire evolution of all of mankind recontextualized the human experience this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.38,1:53:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.38,1:53:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, we did it, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.38,1:53:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to discuss one more analogy, and then we're going to have questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.38,1:53:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One more analogy that really fits in well with A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.64,1:53:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It talks about the innate innocence within each and every, all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.93,1:53:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In the analogy of the computer, you see, consciousness is like the hardware,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.22,1:53:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ego is like the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.28,1:53:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us, the hardware, you see, is uninfluenced by the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.28,1:53:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can play any program through the hardware of a computer,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.28,1:53:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hardware of the computer is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.50,1:53:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not affected by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.43,1:53:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all run by our software,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.43,1:54:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but we never lose the innocence of our hardware.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.43,1:54:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we're all so programmable, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.62,1:54:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of our innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.62,1:54:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the innocence is the opening through which
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.62,1:54:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that which denies spiritual reality can creep in?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.87,1:54:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of our innocence that we're programmable
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.94,1:54:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.72,1:54:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what you say, averse to human happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.72,1:54:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're programmable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.72,1:54:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're programmable because there is no truth switch on our computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.82,1:54:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can program this computer, the human mind, with anything you want on a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.82,1:54:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I recently saw a very interesting series of documentaries on the History Channel
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.81,1:54:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of Hitler's youth, the years when these innocent young children,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.29,1:54:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,how they were brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.15,1:55:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could see,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.15,1:55:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they couldn't help but be other than they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.15,1:55:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They were brought up in this wonderful campfire kind of camaraderie,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.22,1:55:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,singing these wonderful songs for the good of their motherland
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.22,1:55:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pride of their family and culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.22,1:55:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you know, it was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.22,1:55:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How could these kids be anything other than what they were?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.22,1:55:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They loved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.57,1:55:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked forward to going to camp,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.57,1:55:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were all trying to be a better, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.57,1:55:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it was very much like the Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.57,1:55:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,very much like the Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.57,1:55:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that the Scouts went this way and the Hitler youth went that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.57,1:55:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But the techniques were almost identical, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.60,1:55:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,cooking hot dogs by the fire and singing the songs,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.60,1:55:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the camaraderie.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.82,1:55:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we saw the innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.26,1:55:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how innocence is vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.26,1:55:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how innocence is vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.26,1:55:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But the innocence is never lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.67,1:56:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we evolve spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.67,1:56:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we look past the programming,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.67,1:56:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the innocence of the spirit within.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:06.67,1:56:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.67,1:56:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the innocence of the spirit within.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.79,1:56:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spirit cannot be damaged,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.79,1:56:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's when we stop identifying the myself as the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.34,1:56:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, when you stop misidentifying the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.34,1:56:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't like about The Chorus of Miracles is the textbook.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.34,1:56:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The workbook is perfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.53,1:56:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the workbook alone,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.53,1:56:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will take you the whole way.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.01,1:56:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that I disagree with in the textbook
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.10,1:56:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is the way it tends to set up the ego as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.81,1:56:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you get polarized.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.81,1:56:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You get polarized with the ego as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.13,1:56:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, your software is not an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.13,1:56:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.13,1:56:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Two different things.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.70,1:56:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.80,1:57:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.80,1:57:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the problem is not the ego or the software,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.86,1:57:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's identifying with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.86,1:57:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is not the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.86,1:57:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is identifying with the ego itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.86,1:57:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't destroy the ego, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:12.15,1:57:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to set up the ego as your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.15,1:57:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you get into the problem with force, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.15,1:57:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you condemn the ego and fight it as an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:21.98,1:57:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you strengthen it,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.98,1:57:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've polarized it and given it an existence
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.98,1:57:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when it has no existence in reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.98,1:57:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a subtle point,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:30.56,1:57:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is one error, I think, in the textbook,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.75,1:57:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is the proclivity to set up the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.75,1:57:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.23,1:57:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's all I wanted to say about the course
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.42,1:57:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the analogy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.42,1:57:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That intrinsic innocence, then, is our reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:49.54,1:57:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The programming that goes on, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.54,1:57:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that's maintained in the spirit...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.54,1:57:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I read an interesting book.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.54,1:57:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard they were review books,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.54,1:57:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but once in a while I get one,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.54,1:57:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrate its energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.54,1:58:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought, hmm, I'll read this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.54,1:58:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:02.54,1:58:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It came from Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.83,1:58:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was called Omniology by Dr. Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.63,1:58:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody from your industry can be named Lee, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.63,1:58:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how they keep track of each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.69,1:58:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yung Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.69,1:58:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, they all sound like they're all Dr. Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:18.69,1:58:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I must know 20 different Dr. Lees.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.69,1:58:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it was an interesting book.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:23.69,1:58:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.69,1:58:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.69,1:58:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.69,1:58:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the physical body, the mental body,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.69,1:58:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual body,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.69,1:58:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and that part of the spiritual body
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.69,1:58:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is what he calls the...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:35.69,1:58:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He called it the...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.14,1:58:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.54,1:58:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the informational body.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.54,1:58:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.09,1:58:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:48.09,1:58:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the karmic inheritance, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.09,1:58:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the informational body.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.09,1:58:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Your karma comes...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:52.09,1:58:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit continues from lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:54.09,1:58:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,reincarnation to incarnation,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:56.09,1:59:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it picks up the vibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.09,1:59:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of all your decisions, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:03.09,1:59:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it carries that from lifetime to lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:05.09,1:59:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and he calls it the informational body.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.09,1:59:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.09,1:59:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the spirit would be,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.09,1:59:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,like, the programming part.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:14.09,1:59:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.09,1:59:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Each lifetime, you make a decision,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.09,1:59:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and you come from a certain positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.09,1:59:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the next lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.09,1:59:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to pick up,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.09,1:59:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're starting with that set of programs
Dialogue: 0,1:59:23.09,1:59:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:24.09,1:59:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you pick up your own software.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.15,1:59:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You pick up your own software,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:29.15,1:59:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and you continue with it
Dialogue: 0,1:59:30.15,1:59:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,until you realize you're the hardware,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.15,1:59:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,not the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:33.15,1:59:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to keep going through all this
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.15,1:59:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to perfect that software, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.15,1:59:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're not your software,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:38.15,1:59:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in perfecting it,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.15,1:59:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.15,1:59:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.69,1:59:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, any questions?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:43.69,1:59:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.38,1:59:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've never asked it.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.38,1:59:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jesus Christ calibrates at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.70,2:00:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.70,2:00:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean that Jesus Christ couldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:04.02,2:00:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, what I thought was,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.02,2:00:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,my own personal opinion,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:08.02,2:00:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the teachings of Christ
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.02,2:00:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as translatable into human understanding
Dialogue: 0,2:00:13.02,2:00:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at this time would not be above,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.72,2:00:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, 600 is as high as anybody can get
Dialogue: 0,2:00:18.72,2:00:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in this average population.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.72,2:00:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That the teachings themselves could,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:25.23,2:00:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn't necessarily have to teach at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.23,2:00:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because at 1,000 there's really nothing to say.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:33.23,2:00:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only being what you are,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:35.23,2:00:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and being what you are is sufficient
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.23,2:00:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to save all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.23,2:00:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, other than breathing in and out,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.23,2:00:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing to do in 1,000.
